{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "43327d52-861e-4cca-9e6d-24db6344b6fc",
    "name": "RepaySync API",
    "description": "Complete RepaySync REST API collection for managing customers, interactions, and audit logs.\n\n## Getting Started\n1. Collection variables are pre-filled for local `seed_demo` (password `demo123456`).\n2. Run **Authentication → Obtain Token** — tokens are saved automatically.\n3. Run **Customers → List Customers** to capture `customerId`, or **Create Customer**.\n4. All other requests use bearer auth from `accessToken`.\n\n## Demo logins (after `python manage.py seed_demo`)\n| Email | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `manager1@example.com` | Field manager — create/assign customers |\n| `senior@example.com` | Senior manager — bulk users, audit logs |\n| `officer1@example.com` | Collection officer — assigned customers only |\n| `agent1@example.com` | Calling agent — all customers |\n\n## Collection Variables\n| Variable | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `baseUrl` | API base (default `http://localhost:8000/api/v1`) |\n| `email` / `password` | Credentials for Obtain Token |\n| `accessToken` / `refreshToken` | JWT tokens (auto-set) |\n| `customerId` | Customer UUID (auto-set from list/create) |\n| `interactionId` | Interaction UUID (auto-set from create) |\n| `auditLogId` | Audit log UUID (auto-set from list) |\n| `officerEmail` | Target officer for Assign Customer |",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "32181544"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Authentication",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Obtain Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', json.access);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('refreshToken', json.refresh);",
                  "  pm.test('Access token saved', () => pm.expect(json.access).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/token/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "token", ""]
            },
            "description": "Obtain JWT access and refresh tokens. Uses `email` and `password` collection variables (defaults match `seed_demo`)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (json.access) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', json.access);",
                  "    pm.test('New access token saved', () => pm.expect(json.access).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "  }",
                  "  if (json.refresh) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('refreshToken', json.refresh);",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"refresh\": \"{{refreshToken}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/token/refresh/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "token", "refresh", ""]
            },
            "description": "Exchange refresh token for a new access token. Updates `accessToken` automatically."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "JWT authentication. Run **Obtain Token** first."
    },
